    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1866-01-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1866-01-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="384" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d384">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Williams</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Seward</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 23]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,
                                        <hi rend="italic">Peking,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1866-01-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 31, 1866.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: * * * * *</p>
                <p>I have just been informed by Mr. Vlangaly, the Russian minister, that the
                            Chinese government has extended to Russian ships trading between its
                            open ports and the Russian possessions on the Amoor the same privileges
                            in respect to the payment of tonnage dues that have been granted to
                            vessels trading to Japan and Saigon, as mentioned in my despatch (No. 8)
                            of October 5, 1860. The same privilege enures to American as well as
                            other vessels trading between China and the Amoor.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>S. WELLS WILLIAMS, <hi rend="italic">Chargé
                                d’Affaires.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State, Washington, D. C.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
